Article: Best Favorite Moments of Quality Animation in NGE
) and then there's Eva-01 freakout and the animalistic berserk stomping around. THAT is A-tier 90s tv sakuga. - I feel a bit leery about including these since they were animated for feature (Death & Rebirth) so it kinda goes without saying the sakuga in these clips is among the best in television series... ANYWAY. Almost all new DC cuts in eps 22-24 count. New Asuka scenes in ep 22 are all very well animated and Armisael sequence is truly superb through and through - and then it culminates in that fucking Angel Tower... but uhh yeah, obviously all this footage is fantastic but I'm not sure if it's entirely fair to include it. - Eva-01 vs Eva-02 in ep 24. - The morphing shapes and the like in ep 26 are great and were IIRC co-animated entirely by Anno and Masayuki. ******************* That's kinda it for stuff that stands out. For most part animation in NGE gets the job done while it is Anno's directing that elevates series into the aesthetic stratosphere it reaches. Contemporary Escaflowne was much better animated by episode to episode basis but aesthetically it never stands up against average Eva episode (except in music department where Escaflowne stomps all over NGE erry single episode). End of Evangelion is fantastically animated through and through. In particular the whole MPE fight sequence stands even today as THE exhibit of Mitsuo Iso's insane skill and as probably the best mecha action ever put on screen. I think only with Q Rebuild finally matched and arguably bettered EoE in overall animation quality.

[]:             Quote Post by Gendo'sPapa » Mon Apr 28, 2014 8:57 am Never gotten behind the idea that NGE is "badly animated". It's gorgeous animation & has some of the best direction I've ever seen in the animated medium! It may not have the -usually awful - flourishes a lot of other Japanese animus has but it's not some kind of constant eye sore. As Xard says, while NGE had a small budget it was Anno's expertise as a director & his understanding of when to go big with the animation & when to skimp for dramatic effect that helped the show the classic it is today. Favorite animation? As some others have said - I LOVE the stark look to Episode
